1410
01:43:06,847 --> 01:43:08,891
But one must not forget
the most important thing

1411
01:43:08,974 --> 01:43:10,476
-in the nigger-fight game.
-Mm-hmm.

1412
01:43:10,559 --> 01:43:13,479
-And that is a nigger that can win fights.
-Mm-hmm.

1413
01:43:13,854 --> 01:43:18,025
Now, that should be your first,
second, third, fourth and fifth concern.

1414
01:43:18,442 --> 01:43:20,736
Now, after you have that,
and you know you have that,

1415
01:43:20,820 --> 01:43:23,739
then you can start to implement
a grand design.

1416
01:43:24,657 --> 01:43:27,368
In other words, first thing is first.

1417
01:43:27,451 --> 01:43:28,828
First thing's first.

1418
01:43:33,874 --> 01:43:35,835
[whispering in German]

1419
01:43:36,001 --> 01:43:39,505
-[chuckles]
-Ooh! I see you two getting on.

1420
01:43:40,589 --> 01:43:41,632
Famously!

1421
01:43:42,967 --> 01:43:44,802
Oh, Monsieur Candie, you cannot imagine

1422
01:43:44,885 --> 01:43:48,848
what it's like not to hear
your native tongue in four years.

1423
01:43:48,931 --> 01:43:51,100
Well, hell, I can't imagine
two weeks in Boston!

1424
01:43:51,183 --> 01:43:53,269
-[all laughing]
-[Stephen howls with laughter]

1425
01:43:53,394 --> 01:43:56,897
Two weeks in Boston!
[laughs] Monsieur Candie, you a mess.

1426
01:43:56,981 --> 01:43:59,859
[laughs] Two weeks in Boston!

1427
01:44:00,276 --> 01:44:05,573
[Schultz] I can't express the joy I felt
conversing in my mother tongue.

1428
01:44:05,698 --> 01:44:09,910
And Hildi is a charming
conversation companion.

1429
01:44:10,077 --> 01:44:11,954
[Candie] Well, be careful, now,
Dr. Schultz.

1430
01:44:12,413 --> 01:44:14,915
You might've caught yourself
a little dose of nigger-love.

1431
01:44:15,291 --> 01:44:17,626
-Nigger-love's a powerful emotion, boy.
-[Stephen] Mm!

1432
01:44:17,710 --> 01:44:21,130
It's like a pool of black tar.
Once it catches your ass, you caught.

1433
01:44:21,213 --> 01:44:24,091
Yes, sir, you stuck. [chuckles]

1434
01:44:24,258 --> 01:44:25,509
[Lara] I don't know, doctor.

1435
01:44:26,051 --> 01:44:28,763
You can lay on all the German
sweet talk you want, but...

1436
01:44:29,096 --> 01:44:32,683
it looks like this pony's
got big eyes for Django.

1437
01:44:33,392 --> 01:44:34,935
[Lara chuckles]

1438
01:44:35,394 --> 01:44:37,938
Well, naturally!

1439
01:44:38,105 --> 01:44:43,110
It is the soaring eagle that attracts
her attention, not the plucked chicken.

1440
01:44:43,235 --> 01:44:44,653
[all chuckling]

1441
01:44:44,820 --> 01:44:47,531
[Candie] Dr. Schultz, don't be
so down on yourself.

1442
01:44:47,615 --> 01:44:49,450
You are quite
the dapper European gentleman.

1443
01:44:49,533 --> 01:44:52,953
[Cora] You got to clean these dishes.
Put your elbow in these dishes, you hear?

1444
01:44:53,037 --> 01:44:54,663
You know that nigger, don't you?

1445
01:44:56,081 --> 01:44:57,333
-Who?
-"Who?"

1446
01:44:57,458 --> 01:44:59,919
Don't "who" me, bitch.
You know who I'm talking about.

1447
01:45:02,463 --> 01:45:03,464
At the table?

1448
01:45:04,423 --> 01:45:05,591
I don't know him.

1449
01:45:05,966 --> 01:45:07,384
You don't know him.

1450
01:45:07,885 --> 01:45:09,887
-No.
-"No," what?

1451
01:45:10,679 --> 01:45:11,701
No, sir.

1452
01:45:14,058 --> 01:45:15,643
[chuckles]

1453
01:45:16,727 --> 01:45:18,437
You wouldn't lie to me, now, would you?

1454
01:45:22,525 --> 01:45:24,068
[tuts] Okay.

1455
01:45:25,903 --> 01:45:28,614
Yeah. If you say so.

1456
01:45:35,037 --> 01:45:38,332
Eskimo Joe's a quality nigger,
no doubt about it.

1457
01:45:40,125 --> 01:45:41,335
But if it was my money...

1458
01:45:43,212 --> 01:45:45,256
I wouldn't pay no 12,000 dollars for him.

1459
01:45:45,548 --> 01:45:47,091
What would your price be?

1460
01:45:48,008 --> 01:45:49,885
Well, if I was inclined to be generous,

1461
01:45:49,969 --> 01:45:53,055
and I don't know why
I would be inclined to be generous...

1462
01:45:54,515 --> 01:45:55,558
nine thousand.

1463
01:45:57,059 --> 01:45:58,143
Maybe.

1464
01:45:58,864 --> 01:45:59,895
[Candie] Dr. Schultz.

1465
01:46:00,938 --> 01:46:04,650
Let me re-clarify how this whole
negotiation came about.

1466
01:46:05,234 --> 01:46:07,314
It wasn't me who came to you
to sell a nigger.

1467
01:46:07,414 --> 01:46:08,237
Sure wasn't.

1468
01:46:08,320 --> 01:46:11,073
-It was you who approached me to buy one.
-Sure was.

1469
01:46:11,282 --> 01:46:14,118
[Candie] That 9,000 dollars Bright Boy's
been bandying about

1470
01:46:14,201 --> 01:46:17,246
ain't too far off. If I wanted to sell
Eskimo Joe for that

1471
01:46:17,329 --> 01:46:19,540
-I could do so any day of the week.
-Any day.

1472
01:46:20,207 --> 01:46:23,836
But like you said in Greenville, doctor,
I don't wanna sell him.

1473
01:46:24,837 --> 01:46:29,133
It was only your ridiculous offer
of 12,000 dollars

1474
01:46:29,216 --> 01:46:31,385
-that made me even consider it.
-Mm-hm.

1475
01:46:40,185 --> 01:46:44,231
You know, Monsieur Candie,
you do possess the power of persuasion.

1476
01:46:44,732 --> 01:46:45,733
[chuckles]

1477
01:46:47,857 --> 01:46:48,944
[Schultz bangs table]

1478
01:46:49,028 --> 01:46:53,073
Why not? Monsieur Candie, you have a deal.
Eskimo Joe, 12,000 dollars.

1479
01:46:53,157 --> 01:46:56,452
Hooray, doctor. Hooray.
And a wise decision that is.

1480
01:46:56,535 --> 01:46:59,914
However, that is a tremendous
amount of money.

1481
01:47:00,247 --> 01:47:03,417
And the way you have your Mr. Moguy,
I have a lawyer.

1482
01:47:03,584 --> 01:47:05,336
Persnickety man named Tuttle.

1483
01:47:05,628 --> 01:47:08,839
And I would need my Mr. Tuttle
to draw up a legal contract

1484
01:47:08,923 --> 01:47:12,384
before I'd feel comfortable exchanging
that amount of money for flesh.

1485
01:47:12,468 --> 01:47:15,137
-Mm-hmm.
-Not to mention having Eskimo Joe examined

1486
01:47:15,220 --> 01:47:16,555
by a physician of my choosing.

1487
01:47:16,639 --> 01:47:21,727
-[Candie] Naturally.
-So, say I return in about...

1488
01:47:24,772 --> 01:47:26,815
-five days' time.
-Five days?

1489
01:47:27,149 --> 01:47:28,525
With my Mr. Tuttle.

1490
01:47:28,651 --> 01:47:30,819
And then my Mr. Tuttle and your Mr. Moguy

1491
01:47:30,903 --> 01:47:33,197
can hash out the finer details
between themselves.

1492
01:47:34,657 --> 01:47:37,326
I say splendid, doctor. Splendid.

1493
01:47:38,369 --> 01:47:39,476
Gentlemen...

1494
01:47:40,663 --> 01:47:42,289
may I propose a toast?

1495
01:47:44,917 --> 01:47:46,377
To Eskimo Joe.

1496
01:47:46,543 --> 01:47:50,130
Or shall we call him the Black Hercules?

1497
01:47:50,214 --> 01:47:52,716
-[all laughing]
-[Schultz] To the Black Hercules.

1498
01:47:52,841 --> 01:47:55,886
-[Stephen] The Black Hercules!
-The Black Hercules.

1499
01:47:55,970 --> 01:47:58,931
You was right, doctor.
That name do have pan-ass.

1500
01:47:59,014 --> 01:48:00,140
[chuckles]

1501
01:48:00,224 --> 01:48:04,311
Mm. Hildi? Top my drink off.

1502
01:48:07,940 --> 01:48:11,819
So, Hildi, how you like serving
at the big table in the Big House, huh?

1503
01:48:12,987 --> 01:48:15,447
When Monsieur Candie
talk to you, you answers.

1504
01:48:16,448 --> 01:48:18,617
-I like it a lot, Monsieur Candie.
-[Candie] Mm-hmm!

1505
01:48:19,326 --> 01:48:21,245
It's better than sizzling in that hot box

1506
01:48:21,328 --> 01:48:23,580
or dragging your ass
through a bramble bush.

1507
01:48:23,872 --> 01:48:27,042
Maybe not quite as much fun as getting
to pleasure all them Mandingos,

1508
01:48:27,126 --> 01:48:28,919
-huh, sugar bear?
-She like them niggers.

1509
01:48:29,003 --> 01:48:30,963
-Like Samson? Huh?
-[Broomhilda] No, sir.

1510
01:48:31,880 --> 01:48:35,759
You know, Monsieur Candie, the doctor here
might be interested in seeing

1511
01:48:35,968 --> 01:48:39,138
Hildi's peeled back, seeing as how
they don't have many niggers

1512
01:48:39,221 --> 01:48:40,222
where he come from.

1513
01:48:40,556 --> 01:48:42,975
Dr. Schultz, when you was alone
with Hildi, here,

1514
01:48:43,058 --> 01:48:46,311
did you just speak German,
or did you get to take her clothes off?

1515
01:48:46,395 --> 01:48:50,065
-No, we just talked, and--
-[Candie] So you haven't seen her back?

1516
01:48:50,352 --> 01:48:51,400
I haven't.

1517
01:48:51,692 --> 01:48:54,695
No, no, no. Stephen's right,
you might find this interesting.

1518
01:48:54,778 --> 01:48:58,532
Hildi, take off your dress.
Show Dr. Schultz your back, here. Go on.

1519
01:48:58,615 --> 01:49:02,536
[Lara] Uh... Calvin! I just got her
all dressed up and looking nice.

1520
01:49:02,619 --> 01:49:05,748
[Candie] But, Lara Lee,
Dr. Schultz is from Dusseldorf!

1521
01:49:05,831 --> 01:49:08,792
They don't got niggers there.
He is a man of medicine.

1522
01:49:08,876 --> 01:49:11,503
I'm sure it would fascinate him,
the nigger's endurance for pain.

1523
01:49:11,795 --> 01:49:15,132
These niggers are tough,
Dr. Schultz, no doubt about it.

1524
01:49:15,257 --> 01:49:17,760
Hildi's got something like
four lashes on her back.

1525
01:49:17,843 --> 01:49:20,095
Lara Lee just get one,
she'd lose her goddamn mind.

1526
01:49:20,179 --> 01:49:22,181
Look at that, doctor.
It's like a painting.

1527
01:49:22,306 --> 01:49:23,348
[shouting] Calvin!

1528
01:49:24,349 --> 01:49:27,227
[whispering] We are eating. Ain't no-one
wanna look at her whipped-up back.

1529
01:49:29,313 --> 01:49:30,981
Fine. Fine, fine, fine.

1530
01:49:31,690 --> 01:49:33,984
After dinner, then, Stephen. After dinner.

1531
01:49:35,319 --> 01:49:36,987
During the brandies, gentlemen. Hmm?

1532
01:49:43,285 --> 01:49:44,995
[Lara] Cora, come get this girl.

1533
01:49:48,499 --> 01:49:50,375
-She a mess.
-Yes, ma'am.

1534
01:49:51,043 --> 01:49:55,422
Oh. Why are you all undone?
I just got you done up. Come on in here.

1535
01:50:02,262 --> 01:50:06,183
Baby, you on Stephen bad side,
and you need to be on his blind side.

1536
01:50:06,266 --> 01:50:08,018
You say you ain't know him.

1537
01:50:09,645 --> 01:50:11,605
-[Broomhilda] Huh?
-I said...

1538
01:50:12,564 --> 01:50:15,567
you said you ain't know him.

1539
01:50:17,486 --> 01:50:18,490
[Broomhilda] I don't.

1540
01:50:19,446 --> 01:50:20,489
Yes, you do.

1541
01:50:23,075 --> 01:50:24,118
Mr. Stephen...

1542
01:50:25,559 --> 01:50:26,578
I don't.

1543
01:50:27,037 --> 01:50:28,789
Why is you lying to me?

1544
01:50:31,708 --> 01:50:32,748
I ain't.

1545
01:50:33,418 --> 01:50:34,586
Then why is you crying?

1546
01:50:36,255 --> 01:50:37,464
You scaring me.

1547
01:50:38,090 --> 01:50:39,466
Why is I'm scaring you?

1548
01:50:40,175 --> 01:50:41,635
Because you scary.

1549
01:50:43,846 --> 01:50:49,184
[Schultz] <i>To speak German this afternoon</i>
<i>with Hildi was positively soul-enriching.</i>

1550
01:50:49,643 --> 01:50:52,729
[Candie chuckles] Doctor, that warms
my heart to hear that.

1551
01:50:53,313 --> 01:50:55,691
You stay right here.

1552
01:51:01,613 --> 01:51:06,118
[Schultz] You indicated earlier
you'd be willing to part with Hildi.

1553
01:51:06,368 --> 01:51:08,662
Why, yes. Yessirree Bob, I did.

1554
01:51:11,039 --> 01:51:12,291
In that case,

1555
01:51:13,041 --> 01:51:16,670
allow me to propose another proposition.

1556
01:51:17,171 --> 01:51:18,255
I'm all ears.

1557
01:51:18,505 --> 01:51:19,923
Hurry up, goddamn it!

1558
01:51:21,133 --> 01:51:22,509
-Monsieur Candie--
-[Candie] Stephen.

1559
01:51:22,593 --> 01:51:25,679
[bangs table] You just
interrupted Dr. Schultz, here.

1560
01:51:27,181 --> 01:51:29,433
[Stephen] I'm sorry, Dr. Schultz.

1561
01:51:29,516 --> 01:51:32,102
My ears ain't worth a damn, these days.

1562
01:51:32,227 --> 01:51:33,312
Excuse him.

1563
01:51:33,562 --> 01:51:36,273
Monsieur Candie, could I get
a word with you in the kitchen?

1564
01:51:37,566 --> 01:51:39,234
You mean get up out of my chair?

1565
01:51:39,693 --> 01:51:41,486
If'n you could manage it.

1566
01:51:41,862 --> 01:51:45,032
-Why?
-It's about dessert.

1567
01:51:45,115 --> 01:51:46,158
What about dessert?

1568
01:51:47,034 --> 01:51:49,620
I'd rather discuss that in private.

1569
01:51:49,912 --> 01:51:51,830
[chuckling] We're having white cake!

1570
01:51:52,122 --> 01:51:54,458
What sort of melodrama
could be brewing, back there?

1571
01:51:54,750 --> 01:51:59,087
You right, Monsieur Candie, you right.
I'll handle it myself. [chuckles]

1572
01:51:59,254 --> 01:52:00,672
[whispering] Meet me in the library.

1573
01:52:00,839 --> 01:52:04,218
[speaking] I just can't understand
why you won't come talk to these niggers.

1574
01:52:04,301 --> 01:52:06,220
Shit get fucked up around here,
you blame me.

1575
01:52:06,303 --> 01:52:11,016
Fine, fine. Friend Stephen,
I... will be along momentarily.

1576
01:52:11,558 --> 01:52:12,685
Yes, sir.

1577
01:52:13,332 --> 01:52:14,394
[Candie] Well...

1578
01:52:15,520 --> 01:52:19,316
Gentlemen, as you can see, talented
as they are, no doubt, in the kitchen,

1579
01:52:19,399 --> 01:52:23,028
from time to time,
adult supervision is required.

1580
01:52:23,320 --> 01:52:24,905
[all chuckling]

1581
01:52:25,948 --> 01:52:27,282
If you'll excuse me a moment.

1582
01:52:33,914 --> 01:52:35,582
You may clear the dinner service.

1583
01:52:37,167 --> 01:52:40,837
[Cora] <i>You heard him.</i>
<i>Go on, get. Hurry up, girl.</i>

1584
01:52:40,921 --> 01:52:42,089
So, Dr. Schultz...

1585
01:52:43,006 --> 01:52:45,676
why don't you regale us
with a tale of the circus?

1586
01:52:46,385 --> 01:52:48,637
-The circus? [laughs]
-Yes.

1587
01:52:55,394 --> 01:52:56,645
What is the matter?

1588
01:53:02,526 --> 01:53:07,114
Them motherfuckers ain't here
to buy no Mandingos.

1589
01:53:07,739 --> 01:53:09,074
They wants that girl.

1590
01:53:09,366 --> 01:53:10,826
[chuckles]

1591
01:53:11,535 --> 01:53:14,288
Stephen, what the hell
are you talking about? Hmm?

1592
01:53:14,413 --> 01:53:17,332
They playing your ass for a fool,
is what I'm talking about.

1593
01:53:17,958 --> 01:53:21,378
They ain't here
for no muscle-bound Jimmie.

1594
01:53:22,004 --> 01:53:23,297
They here for that girl.

1595
01:53:23,839 --> 01:53:26,383
What... What girl? What, Hildi?

1596
01:53:26,633 --> 01:53:30,262
Yeah, Hildi. Her and Django?
Them niggers know each other.

1597
01:53:32,097 --> 01:53:35,058
-He just bought Eskimo Joe, I--
-Did he give you any money?

1598
01:53:35,309 --> 01:53:37,561
-No, not yet, but--
-Then he ain't bought diddly.

1599
01:53:37,644 --> 01:53:40,981
Not yet, no how.
But he's just about to buy...

1600
01:53:41,481 --> 01:53:44,026
who he come here to buy
when I interrupted him.

1601
01:53:44,776 --> 01:53:47,529
"Thank you, Stephen."
"You're welcome, Calvin."

1602
01:53:53,160 --> 01:53:54,870
Where you getting all this?

1603
01:53:56,371 --> 01:53:59,541
Why would they go through all that trouble
for a nigger with a chewed-up back

1604
01:53:59,624 --> 01:54:00,876
ain't worth 300 dollars?

1605
01:54:01,335 --> 01:54:04,755
They doing it 'cause that nigger Django's
in love with Hildi.

1606
01:54:05,339 --> 01:54:06,465
She probably his wife.

1607
01:54:07,341 --> 01:54:10,344
Now, why that German gives a fuck
who that uppity son of a bitch

1608
01:54:10,427 --> 01:54:12,971
is in love with, I'm sure I don't know.

1609
01:54:16,183 --> 01:54:17,434
If she's who they want...

1610
01:54:18,477 --> 01:54:22,606
why this whole snake oil pitch
about Mandingos, then?

1611
01:54:22,981 --> 01:54:25,984
You wouldn't pay no never mind
to no 300 dollar.

1612
01:54:26,777 --> 01:54:28,278
But that 12,000?

1613
01:54:29,529 --> 01:54:31,573
That made you real friendly,
now, didn't it?

1614
01:54:34,701 --> 01:54:36,078
Yes, it did.

1615
01:54:39,915 --> 01:54:40,955
His wife, huh?

1616
01:54:45,629 --> 01:54:48,799
If it had been a snake,
it would've bit me.

1617
01:54:49,049 --> 01:54:50,384
[chuckles]

1618
01:54:52,552 --> 01:54:54,012
Those lying...

1619
01:54:55,347 --> 01:55:00,977
goddamn time-wasting sons of bitches.

1620
01:55:02,646 --> 01:55:04,481
[claps] Sons of bitches!

1621
01:55:05,023 --> 01:55:07,901
[Lara] ...out of New Orleans,
so I have quite a bit of practice

1622
01:55:08,026 --> 01:55:10,570
with theater types. [chuckles]

1623
01:55:11,321 --> 01:55:14,616
Oh, there you are! I was beginning
to think that you and that old crow

1624
01:55:14,699 --> 01:55:17,744
-run off together.
-[all chuckling]

1625
01:55:17,828 --> 01:55:19,538
That'd be a hell of a note, wouldn't it?

1626
01:55:20,288 --> 01:55:23,041
Lara Lee, I was just looking
out the big window.

1627
01:55:23,250 --> 01:55:26,253
Billy Crash is out there
dealing with some shady slaver

1628
01:55:26,336 --> 01:55:27,754
trying to sell a passel of ponies.

1629
01:55:27,838 --> 01:55:30,757
Would you be a dear, go out there
and give them gals an eyeball?

1630
01:55:31,174 --> 01:55:32,551
-Hmm?
-Of course, brother.

1631
01:55:32,684 --> 01:55:33,987
-Thank you, darling.
-[giggles]

1632
01:55:47,149 --> 01:55:50,485
-Yeah. Business never sleeps.
-Mm-hmm.

1633
01:55:52,904 --> 01:55:57,409
Apropos, before your exit,
we were discussing

1634
01:55:57,492 --> 01:56:00,078
the possibility
of my purchasing Broomhilda.

1635
01:56:00,162 --> 01:56:02,747
Ah, yes. Yes, we were, doctor.

1636
01:56:03,165 --> 01:56:05,292
And we will again, in a moment.

1637
01:56:21,766 --> 01:56:23,226
Who's your little friend?

1638
01:56:26,271 --> 01:56:27,272
[clears throat]

1639
01:56:28,940 --> 01:56:29,983
This is Ben.

1640
01:56:31,735 --> 01:56:35,906
He's a old Joe that lived around here
for a long time.

1641
01:56:36,781 --> 01:56:38,533
And I do mean a long damn time.

1642
01:56:40,494 --> 01:56:43,747
Old Ben here took care of my daddy...

1643
01:56:44,998 --> 01:56:46,374
and my daddy's daddy.

1644
01:56:47,334 --> 01:56:49,294
Till he up and keeled over, one day...

1645
01:56:52,714 --> 01:56:53,924
Old Ben took care of me.

1646
01:56:56,760 --> 01:57:00,805
Growing up the son
of a huge plantation owner in Mississippi

1647
01:57:00,889 --> 01:57:06,394
puts a white man in contact
with a whole lot of black faces.

1648
01:57:08,605 --> 01:57:13,235
I spent my whole life here,
right here in Candyland...

1649
01:57:14,945 --> 01:57:18,281
surrounded by black faces.

1650
01:57:20,825 --> 01:57:23,537
Now, seeing them every day,
day in, day out, I...

1651
01:57:24,412 --> 01:57:25,956
I only had one question.

1652
01:57:30,168 --> 01:57:33,213
-Why don't they kill us?
-[laughs]

1653
01:57:35,757 --> 01:57:37,676
Now, right out there on that porch,

1654
01:57:38,301 --> 01:57:40,428
three times a week for 50 years,

1655
01:57:40,971 --> 01:57:45,016
Old Ben here would shave my daddy
with a straight razor.

1656
01:57:46,268 --> 01:57:51,231
Now, if I was Old Ben, I would've
cut my daddy's goddamn throat

1657
01:57:51,398 --> 01:57:54,442
and it wouldn't have taken me
no 50 years to do it, neither.

1658
01:57:57,487 --> 01:57:58,488
